parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty coolant temperature sensor can cause the engine to shut off unexpectedly, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The coolant temperature gauge on the dashboard suddenly spikes to the high mark
the engine shuts off
the vehicle loses power and acceleration
and the "Coolant Temperature Too High" message appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical system failure can cause the vehicle to shut off unexpectedly, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts off unexpectedly
the battery dies
the electrical system malfunctions
and the "Service Electrical System" error message appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine stalls
the vehicle loses power and acceleration
and the "Coolant Temperature Too High" message appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine overheating and stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power and come to a sudden stop, which can lead to accidents, especially if it occurs on a busy road or highway. This can also cause damage to the engine and other components.
symptoms: Dashboard alert stating "coolant temperature too high"
engine stalls and shuts down
check engine light comes on
service 4WD system and EBS not available alerts
loss of power steering
hard brake pedal
vehicle unable to restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The clutch and transmission issues can cause the vehicle to jerk or hesitate while shifting, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents. This can also cause damage to the transmission and other components.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
vehicle jerks or hesitates while shifting
transmission slips
vehicle unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The auto start/stop system malfunction can cause the vehicle to shut down unexpectedly, which can lead to accidents, especially if it occurs on a busy road or highway. This can also cause inconvenience and delay to the driver.
symptoms: Vehicle shuts down unexpectedly
vehicle unable to restart for a short period
no warning messages or lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The oil leaks and engine knocking can cause engine damage, which can lead to costly repairs and even engine failure.
symptoms: Oil leaks
engine knocking
hissing noise under the hood
clanking noise underneath the catalytic converter.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system malfunction can cause various systems to fail, which can lead to accidents, especially if it occurs on a busy road or highway. This can also cause inconvenience and delay to the driver.
symptoms: Radio screen gets stuck
radio does not shut off after vehicle shuts off
car in park but not recognized by the system
TIMP issues
stop and start function not working properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Uconnect display screen can cause safety concerns, particularly with the rear backup camera, making it difficult for drivers to see when reversing, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The Uconnect screen is glitching
displaying distorted or discolored images
or going entirely black
affecting the backup camera
navigation
and other vehicle controls.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Coolant Temperature High Warning and Engine Shutdown
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shutdown of the engine due to a coolant temperature high warning can cause accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic, as the vehicle may lose power and steering control.
symptoms: The dashboard displays a "Coolant Temp High" or "Coolant Temperature Too High" warning
followed by an immediate engine shutdown
sometimes accompanied by sputtering or stalling of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the stop-start system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down unexpectedly, leading to safety concerns, especially in heavy traffic or when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly shuts down or stalls
sometimes with a warning symbol on the dashboard
and may not restart immediately
causing inconvenience and safety risks.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Acceleration and Emergency Brake Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration and emergency brake malfunction can cause accidents, injuries, and damage to property.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
even when the foot is on the brake
or the emergency brake engages on its own
making it difficult to control the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling or shut-off of the engine can cause loss of control, accidents, and leave the driver stranded, posing a significant risk to safety.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off while driving
often without warning
and may require restarting the vehicle; the vehicle may stall at stop lights
intersections
or while turning; the engine may shut off and restart unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to premature engine wear, engine failure, and potentially cause accidents due to loss of engine power.
symptoms: The vehicle consumes excessive amounts of oil
often requiring frequent oil changes; the vehicle may experience engine stalling or shut-off due to low oil levels.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Issues with the Stop/Start system can cause unexpected engine shut-off, leading to loss of control, accidents, and safety risks.
symptoms: The engine shuts off unexpectedly while driving
often due to the Stop/Start system malfunctioning; the vehicle may experience unusual noises
such as a squeaking sound
when the AC is on and the Stop/Start system engages.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system issues can cause unexpected engine shut-off, loss of control, and accidents, posing a significant risk to safety.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences electrical system malfunctions
such as Check Engine codes
which may not be properly diagnosed or addressed by dealerships; the vehicle may stall or shut off due to electrical system issues.
